{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01FhSVUNMinkrr8mKf97Yj17", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_01TBo3SyhyzaqKfPd3aUKaph", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "for f in evaluator-super-agent agent-eval-harness nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge ux-quality-rubric prototype-creator andy-evan-2026-06-29; do echo \"=== $f ===\"; head -10 ~/second-brain/wiki/$f.md; echo; done", "description": "Read first 10 lines of related wiki pages"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1064, "cache_read_input_tokens": 35832, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1064, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 10}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "5619f843-c6df-4fe5-a5ab-db42a9ff126d", "uuid": "a7f4bb3d-ace2-4bc2-95d2-04e5eae0d19e", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjQTUtAAztDNV9H4B6L", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:37:20.029Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01TBo3SyhyzaqKfPd3aUKaph","type":"tool_result","content":"=== evaluator-super-agent ===\n# Evaluator Super Agent\n\nEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n\n**Status: Shipped.** The evaluator is a 3-phase skill pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator). It has evaluated 18+ STRATs against Jira acceptance criteria with Playwright persona walkthroughs.\n\n## What It Does (current)\n\n| Capability | Source | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n\n=== agent-eval-harness ===\n# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **eval.yaml** — defines execution mode, dataset schema, output descriptions, judges, models, and thresholds\n2. **Dataset** — test cases with realistic inputs for the skill\n3. **Judges** — automated scorers that rate skill outputs against criteria\n4. **Run** — executes the skill against test cases, scores with judges, reports results\n\n=== nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge ===\n# Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge\n\nFirst hands-on internship assignment: apply Nielsen Norman's 10 Usability Heuristics to Kubernetes-style interfaces across multiple AI tools and compare their analysis quality.\n\n## The Jagged Edge\n\nResearch from Harvard Business School shows AI capabilities aren't uniform — models are very good at some tasks and surprisingly bad at others. The boundary between \"good\" and \"bad\" isn't obvious. This is the \"jagged technological frontier.\"\n\n## What Was Tested\n\n\n=== ux-quality-rubric ===\n# UX Quality Rubric\n\nThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n\n## Dimensions (0–2 each, 8 total)\n\n| Dimension | What It Measures |\n|---|---|\n| **Completeness** | Does the prototype cover the RFE's user stories and acceptance criteria? |\n| **Usability** | Is the interaction pattern clear and free of obvious friction? (Nielsen's 10 heuristics) |\n\n=== prototype-creator ===\n# Prototype Creator\n\nPhase 2 (\"the SHOW\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Takes RFE user stories and produces rapid prototypes that make the proposed experience tangible before engineering commits.\n\n## What It Does\n\nGiven an RFE from the [RFE Creator](rfe-creator.md) pipeline or Jira directly, this pipeline:\n\n1. **Create** — Generates a prototype from RFE user stories at a specified fidelity level\n2. **Review** — Scores against a 4-dimension [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)\n\n=== andy-evan-2026-06-29 ===\n# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 29, 2026\n\n1:1 covering prototype evaluator progress, reporting infrastructure, repository strategy, and future directions.\n\n## Key Discussion Points\n\n- **Persona walkthroughs separated:** Fixed overlap issue. Developing \"Findings\" tab documenting issues and resolutions. Implementing \"Auto-fix\" vs \"Report-only\" modes to manage regressions.\n- **Data discrepancies:** Patient scores fluctuating without clear explanation. Investigating inconsistencies.\n- **Jira entity confusion:** Clarified RF (Product Managers create) → Strat relationship. Prototype Creator should ideally link to RF (upstream). \"UI Direction\" section in Strat documents remains useful for prototyping.\n- **Token optimization:** Configure AI to extract only necessary sections (e.g., \"UI Direction\") rather than ingesting entire Strat documents. Need to confirm if it's a hardcoded heading.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5619f843-c6df-4fe5-a5ab-db42a9ff126d","uuid":"88bfcb22-a320-4ca7-89ca-2273292d473a","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:37:20.128Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== evaluator-super-agent ===\n# Evaluator Super Agent\n\nEvan's primary assignment: build an evaluation agent that automates prototype quality assessment within the [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) pipeline.\n\n**Status: Shipped.** The evaluator is a 3-phase skill pipeline on branch `evan/prototype-evaluate` at [andybraren/prototype-creator](https://github.com/andybraren/prototype-creator). It has evaluated 18+ STRATs against Jira acceptance criteria with Playwright persona walkthroughs.\n\n## What It Does (current)\n\n| Capability | Source | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n\n=== agent-eval-harness ===\n# Agent Eval Harness\n\nA framework for evaluating AI agent skill quality through automated testing, judge scoring, and iterative optimization.\n\n## How It Works\n\n1. **eval.yaml** — defines execution mode, dataset schema, output descriptions, judges, models, and thresholds\n2. **Dataset** — test cases with realistic inputs for the skill\n3. **Judges** — automated scorers that rate skill outputs against criteria\n4. **Run** — executes the skill against test cases, scores with judges, reports results\n\n=== nielsens-heuristics-jagged-edge ===\n# Nielsen's Heuristics & The Jagged Edge\n\nFirst hands-on internship assignment: apply Nielsen Norman's 10 Usability Heuristics to Kubernetes-style interfaces across multiple AI tools and compare their analysis quality.\n\n## The Jagged Edge\n\nResearch from Harvard Business School shows AI capabilities aren't uniform — models are very good at some tasks and surprisingly bad at others. The boundary between \"good\" and \"bad\" isn't obvious. This is the \"jagged technological frontier.\"\n\n## What Was Tested\n\n\n=== ux-quality-rubric ===\n# UX Quality Rubric\n\nThe scoring system used by [Prototype Creator](prototype-creator.md) to evaluate generated prototypes. Scored by a restricted `prototype-scorer` agent (no shell, no network, no MCP).\n\n## Dimensions (0–2 each, 8 total)\n\n| Dimension | What It Measures |\n|---|---|\n| **Completeness** | Does the prototype cover the RFE's user stories and acceptance criteria? |\n| **Usability** | Is the interaction pattern clear and free of obvious friction? (Nielsen's 10 heuristics) |\n\n=== prototype-creator ===\n# Prototype Creator\n\nPhase 2 (\"the SHOW\") of Red Hat's [AI-SDLC Pipeline](ai-sdlc-pipeline.md). Takes RFE user stories and produces rapid prototypes that make the proposed experience tangible before engineering commits.\n\n## What It Does\n\nGiven an RFE from the [RFE Creator](rfe-creator.md) pipeline or Jira directly, this pipeline:\n\n1. **Create** — Generates a prototype from RFE user stories at a specified fidelity level\n2. **Review** — Scores against a 4-dimension [UX Quality Rubric](ux-quality-rubric.md)\n\n=== andy-evan-2026-06-29 ===\n# Andy/Evan Meeting -- June 29, 2026\n\n1:1 covering prototype evaluator progress, reporting infrastructure, repository strategy, and future directions.\n\n## Key Discussion Points\n\n- **Persona walkthroughs separated:** Fixed overlap issue. Developing \"Findings\" tab documenting issues and resolutions. Implementing \"Auto-fix\" vs \"Report-only\" modes to manage regressions.\n- **Data discrepancies:** Patient scores fluctuating without clear explanation. Investigating inconsistencies.\n- **Jira entity confusion:** Clarified RF (Product Managers create) → Strat relationship. Prototype Creator should ideally link to RF (upstream). \"UI Direction\" section in Strat documents remains useful for prototyping.\n- **Token optimization:** Configure AI to extract only necessary sections (e.g., \"UI Direction\") rather than ingesting entire Strat documents. Need to confirm if it's a hardcoded heading.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
